{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nEvery gate row and all post-ship dogfooding in this epic needs standing outcome\ninstrumentation: today nothing routinely ties plan-review verdicts to downstream outcomes\n(post-claim edits, reopens, force-closes, verifier FAILs), so false-positive drift stays\ninvisible until it burns author trust (the Tricorder <10% blocking-FP cliff). E1 froze the\nper-ticket **outcome corpus** (`runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl`, 628 rows) and the miner that\nproduces it; this ticket turns that one-shot artifact into a **re-runnable gate-eval job** that\nclassifies each reviewed ticket, emits trailing per-criterion FP-proxy metrics, and documents\nthe alarm/demotion playbook.\n\n## What\nCommit a re-runnable **gate-eval instrumentation job** at\n`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py`.\n\n**Corpus acquisition (subprocess, not import).** The job refreshes the outcome corpus by\ninvoking `mine_outcome_corpus.py` **as a subprocess** (`python <harnesses>/mine_outcome_corpus.py`,\nwhich atomically writes `runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl`), then reads that JSONL. It does NOT\n`import` and call `build_corpus()`, because that entry calls `sys.exit()` on floor-check failure\n(`mine_outcome_corpus.py:381`), which would terminate the caller; and the miner lives in a\nnon-package `harnesses/` dir, so subprocess-by-path is also the clean invocation. A\n`--no-refresh` flag skips regeneration and reads the committed corpus (offline / CI use). It\nthen reads each reviewed ticket's persisted `REVIEW_RESULT` sidecars via\n`rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar.all_review_results`.\n\n**Outcome classifier (deterministic; the honest finding is that the sidecar findings do NOT\ncarry the separating signal).** Investigation against the 8 §5.2 cases proved a classifier over\nthe sidecar findings *alone* reaches only **4/8** — the CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED cases (c8cc, f5df)\nhave finding profiles at or *below* the MISSED cases, because \"caught-but-ignored\" is a fact\nabout the author's **post-claim edit**, not about what the gate saw. The separating signal lives\nin two outcome-corpus fields plus one sidecar-derived strength predicate. The classifier is a\nfirst-match cascade, applied ONLY to tickets with `had_persisted_review` AND a post-claim signal\n(`post_claim_edit_class != \"none\"` OR `review_round_count >= 2`); all others are **N/A**:\n\n```\nC1  post_claim_edit_class == \"operator-attested-retag\"  → CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED\nC2  review_round_count >= 2                              → CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED\nC3  has_strong_finding                                   → UNKNOWABLE\nC4  else                                                 → MISSED\n```\n- `review_round_count` is the **git-walk outcome-corpus** count (true count), not the pruned\n  on-disk sidecar count.\n- **`has_strong_finding`** (the exact \"substantive advisory\" predicate): ∃ a surfaced sidecar\n  finding with `decision ∈ {\"block\",\"advisory\"}` AND `priority >= 0.5` AND\n  `severity ∈ {\"critical\",\"major\"}`. The 0.5 floor is the codebase's own `RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY`\n  (`src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py:299`); the severity conjunct excludes\n  high-priority-but-procedural (P6/P9) findings.\n\nThis **core** cascade reproduces the 8 frozen labels at **7/8** (only c8cc, a lone\n`substantive-unclassified` case, misclassifies as MISSED). A `substantive-unclassified → CAUGHT`\nrule would reach 8/8 but rests on that single case, so it is **deliberately excluded** as\noverfitting and documented as such. The README states plainly that the classifier separates via\noutcome-corpus fields + a sidecar strength predicate, NOT via sidecar findings alone (which\nachieve only 4/8) — the load-bearing methodological finding.\n\n**adverse post-claim edit** (used by both the classifier gate and the metrics below) is defined\nonce: `post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"ac-strengthened\",\n\"substantive-unclassified\"}` (the substantive classes; `operator-attested-retag` is handled by\nC1; `cosmetic`/`none` are not adverse).\n\n**Per-criterion trailing metrics (FINDING-level, matching the parent epic's definition).** Over\nthe trailing window (see `--window`), joining each `REVIEW_RESULT` finding to its ticket's\noutcome row by `ticket_id`, for each criterion C:\n- **blocking_fp_proxy(C)** = (# of C's **blocking** findings whose ticket was subsequently\n  adjudicated not-block-worthy) / (total # of C's blocking findings). The automatic proxy for\n  \"adjudicated not-block-worthy\" is **`force_close OR reopen_count > 0`** (an explicit gate\n  bypass, or a post-close reopen). The earlier `(no adverse post-claim edit)` disjunct is\n  **removed**: blocking findings are remediated *pre-claim* in the review loop, so ~95% of\n  tickets legitimately have `post_claim_edit_class == \"none\"`, and that disjunct would fire on\n  nearly every honored block and mislabel it FP. This proxy is therefore a deliberately\n  conservative **lower bound** (force-close can also happen for orthogonal operator-attestation\n  reasons, ADR 0043), so the >10% alarm **triggers human review** of that criterion's recent\n  blocks rather than an automatic demotion. Per-FINDING, matching the parent's \"fraction of that\n  criterion's blocking findings … subsequently adjudicated not-block-worthy.\"\n- **advisory_application_rate(C)** = (# of C's **advisory** findings whose ticket later shows an\n  adverse post-claim edit) / (total # of C's advisory findings).\n- **rounds_per_ticket** = the `review_round_count` distribution over the window.\n\n**`--window N`** bounds the corpus to the last `N` rows in the miner's deterministic emission\norder (the corpus has no timestamp field; emission order is the stable proxy, documented as\nsuch — a strictly chronological window is future work needing a timestamp). Default N=200.\n\n**Alarm / demotion rule (documented playbook).** When a criterion's trailing\n**blocking_fp_proxy exceeds 10%**, demote it from blocking to advisory via an ordinary\n`criteria_routing.json` edit (`default_posture: \"advisory\"`). Precedent for demotion on FP\nevidence: **T5e**, demoted to advisory in calibration-3 (task relishable-ammonitic-hoverfly).\n(T3/T10 are a *different* precedent — criteria kept non-blocking from the start; never demoted —\nso they are NOT cited as demotion precedent.) Dogfood monitoring, not a config flag; no\ngate/source behaviour change.\n\n## Scope\n- `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py` — the job: a pure\n  top-level `classify(post_claim_edit_class, review_round_count, has_strong_finding) -> str`\n  (unit-testable), the `has_strong_finding` sidecar extractor, the finding-level metrics\n  computation, and CLI flags `--verify-repro`, `--emit`, `--window N`, `--no-refresh`.\n- `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md` — classifier rules, the 4/8-vs-7/8 finding, the\n  metric definitions + join key, cadence, and the metrics output path.\n- `docs/plan-review-gate.md` — the alarm/demotion playbook (>10% blocking-FP rule, T5e\n  precedent, operator response). The ONLY change outside `docs/experiments/`; documentation only.\n- `tests/unit/test_gate_eval_classifier.py` — a golden test importing the pure `classify` and\n  asserting the 8 frozen `(cls, rounds, strong) → label` tuples reproduce ≥6/8, plus a\n  non-triviality assertion on a metrics fixture and a `--window` subset check.\n- No change to `src/rebar/` behaviour — no gate or source behaviour change.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `--verify-repro` recomputes the classifier over the 8 frozen cases (MISSED: dc58-af7b,\n      db7b-c8fd, 5886-d028; CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED: c8cc-68b8, f5df-0069, 115b-ceea, 8c4f-b81c;\n      UNKNOWABLE: 3006-e198), prints the confusion table, and asserts **≥6/8 agreement** (exits\n      non-zero below 6/8). Proving command:\n      `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py --verify-repro`.\n- [ ] `--emit` writes per-criterion metrics to\n      `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json` — a non-trivial object with\n      ≥1 criterion whose `blocking_fp_proxy` and `advisory_application_rate` are **numeric**\n      (a float in [0,1], not null) and whose `sample_counts` is a non-empty dict with a\n      **positive total** (so the AC is NOT satisfiable by `{}`, all-null values, or all-zero\n      sample counts). Proving command:\n      `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py --emit && python -c \"import json;d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json'));assert d and any(isinstance(v.get('blocking_fp_proxy'),(int,float)) and isinstance(v.get('advisory_application_rate'),(int,float)) and isinstance(v.get('sample_counts'),dict) and sum(v['sample_counts'].values())>0 for v in d.values())\"`.\n- [ ] The pure `classify` reproduces ≥6/8 on the 8 frozen input tuples in a CI-collected test,\n      and `--window N` yields a subset for smaller N. Proving command:\n      `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_gate_eval_classifier.py -q`.\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` gains a new **\"Blocking-FP-proxy demotion\"** section\n      documenting the >10% `blocking_fp_proxy` alarm rule, the operator demotion response, and the\n      correct T5e precedent (not T3/T10, cited inside that section); the harnesses README\n      documents the `sidecar-findings-alone` 4/8-vs-7/8 finding. Proving command (both sentinels\n      are new content — neither pre-exists in its file, verified by `grep -c`):\n      `grep -q \"Blocking-FP-proxy demotion\" docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q \"sidecar-findings-alone\" docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/README.md`.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; landed through Gerrit."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784257103517315001,"uuid":"dc9abb9f-5b20-4ff6-9e14-e609d920fe53"}